  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "JK",
    "text": "His name is Jeff Grant. The lady in blue to the left of Susan is my sister, Judy Boyman. Then we have my wife, Virginia. Next to her and on the left, the young boy, is my son, Paul Kempler. On the other side next to Jeff Grant is David, my older son. This was taken in Queens, New York, roughly about 1980. I can't remember the exact date. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The picture on the right is my son David and his wife Peggy. They were married about 1990 up in Incline Village, Nevada. The photo on the left is my younger son, Paul, who was born in 1967, and his wife, April. They were married in November 1993 here in Glendale. Live now in Reno, Nevada. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Neither one of my sons have any children. However, David here, and his wife, just announced that Peggy is three months pregnant. So we look forward to another grandchild. [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] These are pictures of my grandchildren, of my daughter-- the children of my daughter, Susan. This was taken place-- taken in Queens on Long Island, New York. And their names are-- the older one on the left is Andrew. The little one on the right is Brian. This picture is about five years old. So I would say it is taken about 1990.",
